response.about:
2016 Edit: Non-UCL students are more than welcome, our events are attended by Kazakhs from a range of universities around London: LSE, Imperial College London, Westminster, City, King's and many more! So please don't be discouraged by the society's relation to UCL Union - we are open to everyone and are looking forward to meeting you! ;)

Kazakh Society UCLU is your main link to Kazakhstan and Kazakhstani students while you are studying at UCL. It was established in spring 2008 and officially affiliated in autumn of the same year.

The aim of the Kazakh Society is to bring together students around UCL who are particularly interested in culture, history, arts, language, science, as well as politics of the Republic of Kazakhstan. Moreover, to unite Kazakhstani students, find friends and mainly just have fun! The Society organises wide range of events such as concerts, parties, film nights, outside gatherings, sport games and many more!
